  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The National Union of Mineworkers said an estimated 200,000 black gold and coal miners in South Africa will begin a strike Sunday 08/09/1987 night for higher wages and better working conditions.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The union is demanding a 30%, wage increase.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   In addition, the union is demanding pay for black miners doing dangerous work.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The black miners also are asking for 30 days' leave each year, and a paid holiday on June 16, the anniversary of the 1976 Soweto riots.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   They also want an increase in death benefits to five years from two.
  </a>
